## **Description**
The **NodeSelector **operator allows to select data from the input node instance based on the configuration settings.

## **Input**
Input

**Data type**

**Description**

**node**

Any

The node for which the operator will return the instance selected based on the settings

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**out0**

Any

The instance data selected from the input node, based on the settings

## **Settings**
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

- Select the input node instance that the operator will return:

**Select instance**: manually specify the required instance in the **Instance **field below, by entering the numeric value corresponding to the node instance.

- **Select last instance**: select the last instance recorded by the system during runtime.

- Select how to handle errors:

**Default string value on error**: manually specify the value that the operator will return in case of errors in the **Value **field below, by entering the required string.

- **No output on error**: select this option if you do not want the operator to return any value in case of errors.

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

## **Special cases**
In special cases, the operator behaves as follows:

**Case**

**Behavior**

**NULL input (no input)**

The operator does not consider a NULL input. The system logs a warning event.

**The instance typed by the user is larger than the number of repetitions of the node**

The operator returns an empty string.
